---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@components/container.astro";
import Sectionhead from "@components/sectionhead.astro";
---

<Layout title="Chapters">
  <Container>
    <Sectionhead>
      <Fragment slot="title">Chapters Overview</Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="desc">
        Explore <strong>Kubernetes Recipes</strong> â€” practical, hands-on chapters that tackle real-world Kubernetes challenges. Click each chapter to expand for more info.
      </Fragment>
    </Sectionhead>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-16 space-y-4 text-slate-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 1: Getting Started</summary>
        Learn how to set up Kubernetes environments using tools like Minikube, k3s, and kubeadm. A foundational guide to cluster setup and basic operations.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 2: Configuring Stateless Applications</summary>
        Covers namespaces, pods, environment variables, multi-container setups, secrets, and configuration strategies for non-persistent workloads.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 3: Configuring Stateful Applications</summary>
        Focuses on databases, data persistence, migrations, SDLC best practices, and handling complex workloads.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 4: Kubernetes on Cloud Providers</summary>
        Step-by-step deployment on GKE, AKS, EKS, and other providers, plus tools like Kubespray and Sonobuoy for conformance testing.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 5: Developer Experience in Kubernetes</summary>
        Enhance your development workflow using tools like Lens, DevSpace, and VS Code integrated with Kubernetes.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 6: Scaling and Resiliency</summary>
        Techniques for autoscaling (HPA, VPA, KEDA), resource optimization, and deployment strategies using Karpenter and vCluster.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 7: Storage in Kubernetes</summary>
        Explore static/dynamic provisioning, NFS, persistent disks across cloud platforms, and custom StorageClasses.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 8: Networking in Kubernetes</summary>
        In-depth discussion on service types, traffic routing, Istio, network policies, and troubleshooting.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 9: Performance Observability in Kubernetes</summary>
        Learn observability tools including Prometheus, Grafana, ELK, Fluentd, OpenTelemetry, and Cloud-specific monitors.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 10: Control Plane Administration and Package Management</summary>
        Administration of core components (kubelet, scheduler, etc.), node operations, upgrades, and using Helm for packages.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 11: Security in Kubernetes</summary>
        Covers secrets management, RBAC, PodSecurity, AppArmor, Seccomp, and securing clusters with Istio.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 12: Emerging and Advanced Kubernetes Concepts</summary>
        Looks at FaaS, WebAssembly, HPC, CRDs, and deploying AI/ML workloads, including MLOps and air-gapped DevOps.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 13: Best Practices in Kubernetes</summary>
        Offers practical advice on resource limits, health checks, namespaces, multi-tenancy, and immutable infrastructure.
      </details>

      <details class="border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Chapter 14: Additional Kubernetes Resources</summary>
        Highlights CNCF resources, community involvement, sustainability, KubeCon, and tools like Kepler.
      </details>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>
